=Anna M. Shields (1966-)=
===Keywords===
* [[元稹]] [[花間集]]
==Publications==
===Monographs===
* Crafting a Collection: The Cultural Contexts and Poetic Practice of the Huajian ji 花間集 (Collection from Among the Flowers). Harvard East Asian monographs 263, Harvard: Harvard University Press, 2006
===Articles===
* Gathering the 'Flowers' of Poetry and Song: An Analysis of Three Anthologies from the Late Tang and Shu. T'ang Studies 15-16, 1997-1998, pp. 1-39
* Defining Experience: The "Poems of Seductive Allure" (Yanshi) of the Mid-Tang Poet Yuan Zhen (779-831). JAOS,  Volume 122, No. 1, 2002, pp. 61-78
* The Limits of Knowledge: Three Han Yu Letters to Friends, 799-802. T'ang Studies, Volume 22, 2004, pp. 41-80
* Words for the Dead and the Living: Innovations in the Mid-Tang ‘Prayer Text’ (Jiwen). T’ang Studies, Volume 25, 2007, pp. 111-146
===Reviews===
* The Poetics of Decadence: Chinese Poetry of the Southern Dynasties and Late Tang Periods by Fusheng Wu. JAOS, Volume 120, No. 3, 2000, pp. 469-471
* A Chinese Literary Mind: Culture, Creativity, and Rhetoric in "Wenxin diaolong" by Zong-qi Cai. JAOS, Volume 62, No. 2, 2003, pp. 577-580